1
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:08,657
[ Fire crackling ]

2
00:00:14,864 --> 00:00:16,598
[ Horse neighs ]

3
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:21,403
[ Horses neighing ]

4
00:00:29,479 --> 00:00:33,082
[ Speaking native language ]

5
00:00:33,149 --> 00:00:39,154
Walt, the old man says,
"This way of life is not easy."

6
00:00:39,222 --> 00:00:42,891
It is a way of life
for the strong heart.

7
00:00:46,863 --> 00:00:48,664
[ Horse neighs ]

8
00:00:58,441 --> 00:01:02,044
"This sacred lodge
is our original home

9
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:03,712
from our mother earth."

10
00:01:03,780 --> 00:01:05,748
"Coming in,

11
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:08,083
you will leave behind
all that is bad."

12
00:01:11,688 --> 00:01:12,788
[ Horse neighing ]

13
00:01:24,701 --> 00:01:26,435
[ Speaking native language ]

14
00:01:26,536 --> 00:01:28,804
"Stay true
to your warrior spirit."

15
00:01:30,607 --> 00:01:32,040
"Know when to fight
and when to --"

16
00:01:32,142 --> 00:01:34,643
[ telephone ringing ]

17
00:01:38,782 --> 00:01:40,182
[ Walt sighs ]

18
00:01:40,283 --> 00:01:42,651
This is why
I don't have a cellphone.

19
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:46,989
Ruben, do not
bring that phone in here.

20
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:48,924
It's for the sheriff.

21
00:02:03,273 --> 00:02:06,375
[ Police radio chatter ]

22
00:02:12,348 --> 00:02:17,219
[ Door beeping ]

23
00:02:59,062 --> 00:03:02,397
I was starting to worry
about you, sheriff.

24
00:03:02,499 --> 00:03:05,634
She the only horse
that made it out?

25
00:03:05,702 --> 00:03:07,503
Looks that way.

26
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,938
For sure there are
two dead horses inside.

27
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:11,673
This one here's likely
to be the third,

28
00:03:11,774 --> 00:03:13,141
given the severity
of the burns.

29
00:03:14,844 --> 00:03:16,879
Whatever it takes.

30
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:18,280
[ Snorts ]

31
00:03:18,348 --> 00:03:21,416
Don't you listen to branch.

32
00:03:25,054 --> 00:03:27,389
[ Police radio chatter ]

33
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:34,229
What a shit storm.

34
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:37,132
[ Sighs ] That Bill Hoback?

35
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,300
What's he doing here?

36
00:03:38,401 --> 00:03:39,935
He's the Stewarts' neighbor.

37
00:03:40,036 --> 00:03:41,870
He lives five miles that way.

38
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:43,872
But he saw the lights,
heard the sirens,

39
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,908
and came over to see
if he could help.

40
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:47,042
Where's Ray?

41
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:49,845
The husband?
Nobody seems to know.

42
00:03:49,913 --> 00:03:51,713
[ Sighs ] That's his truck
over there.

43
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:53,916
Yeah. I've been
calling his cell all night.

44
00:03:53,983 --> 00:03:56,285
No answer.

45
00:03:56,352 --> 00:03:58,820
Excuse me.
Sheriff Longmire?

46
00:03:58,922 --> 00:04:00,656
I think there's a body inside.

47
00:04:00,757 --> 00:04:02,658
I mean, it's hard to tell
with the smoke and the ash,

48
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:04,259
and that roof
could come down any second.

49
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:05,894
You can't go in.
It's just not safe.

50
00:04:05,962 --> 00:04:07,396
It's better
to wait until morning.

51
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,965
If there's a body in there,
then we're going inside.

52
00:04:10,066 --> 00:04:12,200
No. <i>We</i> are not.

53
00:04:12,302 --> 00:04:13,702
I am.

54
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:15,938
Sheriff, least wear my hat.

55
00:04:16,039 --> 00:04:18,574
No, thanks.
I got one.

56
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,868
[ Grunting ]

57
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:53,742
[ Police radio chatter ]

58
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:57,279
Hey, Bill.

59
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:02,851
Can you take T.J. inside
for a few minutes?

60
00:05:02,952 --> 00:05:04,286
[ Clears throat ]

61
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:07,589
T.J., why don't you, uh,
help me find something to eat

62
00:05:07,690 --> 00:05:09,925
for all these
firefighters here?

63
00:05:10,026 --> 00:05:11,093
It's okay.

64
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,028
Let's see what you got inside.

65
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:18,333
Ray is gonna be devastated.

66
00:05:21,971 --> 00:05:24,139
He loves those horses.
They're his life.

67
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,208
Have you been
able to reach Ray?

68
00:05:26,309 --> 00:05:28,076
I left him messages
on his cell.

69
00:05:28,177 --> 00:05:29,511
No.

70
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:43,992
Where did you get that?

71
00:05:45,361 --> 00:05:48,030
In the barn.
I'm afraid --

72
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:50,932
That's his watch!

73
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,368
Oh, God.

74
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:58,206
[ Voice breaking ]
Oh, God. No.

75
00:05:58,274 --> 00:06:02,644
[ Crying ] Oh, God. Oh, God.
Oh, God, what happened?!

76
00:06:02,712 --> 00:06:05,180
The sun is gonna come up,
and when it does,

77
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:06,748
I promise to find out.

78
00:06:06,816 --> 00:06:12,020
No. [ Crying ]
Oh, my God.

79
00:06:12,088 --> 00:06:16,992
Oh, my God.

80
00:06:17,093 --> 00:06:18,460
[ Crying ]

81
00:06:25,268 --> 00:06:26,334
T.J.!

82
00:06:26,436 --> 00:06:28,136
She needs to be put down.

83
00:06:28,204 --> 00:06:30,272
Hold up.
T.J., let's talk!

84
00:06:30,373 --> 00:06:33,909
Son, put down the gun!
He's okay. He's okay.

85
00:06:38,748 --> 00:06:41,683
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Easy, easy.

86
00:06:41,751 --> 00:06:43,218
No, it's selfish
to keep her alive

87
00:06:43,286 --> 00:06:44,486
when she's like this.

88
00:06:44,587 --> 00:06:46,555
Move out of the way.
[ Gun cocks ]

89
00:06:48,257 --> 00:06:49,825
No!
[ Gunshot ]

90
00:07:10,179 --> 00:07:11,780
[ Vic sniffs ]

91
00:07:11,881 --> 00:07:13,915
[ Sighs ]

92
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:21,523
Room service.

93
00:07:22,892 --> 00:07:25,026
You know, I've seen
some messed up shit on the job,

94
00:07:25,094 --> 00:07:27,162
but this is
my first horse fire.

95
00:07:27,263 --> 00:07:29,197
Sure as hell hope it's my last.

96
00:07:42,278 --> 00:07:43,912
Winston Churchill once said,

97
00:07:44,013 --> 00:07:48,750
"The outside of a horse is
good for the inside of a man."

98
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:54,222
This guy raise racehorses?

99
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:55,957
Nope. Cutting horses.

100
00:07:58,294 --> 00:07:59,761
All those trophies --

101
00:07:59,862 --> 00:08:02,964
these horses
must have been worth a lot.

102
00:08:03,032 --> 00:08:04,966
Body's over there
under those stairs.

103
00:08:05,034 --> 00:08:07,302
[ Coughs ]

104
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:17,779
Now I see why
Ray didn't answer his cellphone.

105
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:26,488
[ Clattering ]

106
00:08:28,157 --> 00:08:30,959
.45.

107
00:08:34,297 --> 00:08:36,298
All the rounds went off.

108
00:08:36,399 --> 00:08:40,202
But only one spent primer,
so one round was fired,

109
00:08:40,303 --> 00:08:42,571
and the others
exploded from the heat.

110
00:08:42,672 --> 00:08:44,973
I'm guessing he took one
to the head.

111
00:08:49,078 --> 00:08:50,979
Give me a hand here.

112
00:08:56,352 --> 00:08:58,453
Going up?
Yep.

113
00:08:58,521 --> 00:09:00,288
[ Both grunt ]

114
00:09:00,356 --> 00:09:02,224
Padlock on the inside.

115
00:09:02,325 --> 00:09:03,425
[ Chain rattles ]

116
00:09:03,526 --> 00:09:05,360
Looks like Ray

117
00:09:05,428 --> 00:09:08,163
didn't want anyone
to get inside to help him.

118
00:09:08,264 --> 00:09:10,732
Looks that way.

119
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:17,572
Alice: What have you found?
What happened?

120
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,574
It's still early,
Mrs. Stewart.

121
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:22,177
But I called a friend of mine from
the insurance company to come out,

122
00:09:22,278 --> 00:09:25,380
take a look around,
and help us sort this out, so...

123
00:09:25,448 --> 00:09:27,549
Now, there will
likely be an autopsy.

124
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,551
I'll push to
have that happen today.

125
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,152
Thank you.

126
00:09:31,254 --> 00:09:34,389
So, was Ray under
any particular pressure lately?

127
00:09:34,457 --> 00:09:37,359
He was --
he was preparing

128
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:39,294
for a big competition
in Houston.

129
00:09:40,463 --> 00:09:42,430
He loved those horses.

130
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,567
But...

131
00:09:45,635 --> 00:09:47,469
What?

132
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:51,673
Well, last week he --
he asked a doctor

133
00:09:51,741 --> 00:09:53,975
to prescribe him
some antidepressants.

134
00:09:54,076 --> 00:09:56,211
I for-- I forget the name,
but I think they're upstairs

135
00:09:56,279 --> 00:09:57,913
in the medicine cabinet.

136
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:02,751
Uh, deputy Moretti,
would you...?

137
00:10:07,290 --> 00:10:10,659
So, Alice...

138
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,560
You know I have to
ask you about it.

139
00:10:12,662 --> 00:10:14,596
Sorry. About what?

140
00:10:14,664 --> 00:10:16,498
You came to me two years ago.

141
00:10:16,565 --> 00:10:18,333
That was a misunderstanding.

142
00:10:18,401 --> 00:10:19,801
He hit you.

143
00:10:19,902 --> 00:10:21,469
I know you didn't
want to press charges,

144
00:10:21,570 --> 00:10:23,238
but you told me he hit you.

145
00:10:23,306 --> 00:10:26,141
So I have to ask --
was it happening again?

146
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,642
That was
a one-time thing.

147
00:10:27,743 --> 00:10:31,146
I swear, sheriff.
Ray loved me.

148
00:10:31,213 --> 00:10:33,014
Now, you asked me
to keep it a secret.

149
00:10:33,115 --> 00:10:35,817
And I have.
But I need to know --

150
00:10:35,918 --> 00:10:38,420
Did anybody else
know about that incident?

151
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:40,956
Say, T.J.?

152
00:10:43,659 --> 00:10:45,360
What is it, sweetheart?

153
00:10:45,461 --> 00:10:47,295
I was going through dad's desk

154
00:10:47,363 --> 00:10:50,098
and I found this note
underneath the keyboard.

155
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:54,302
My name was on the envelope,
and yours was, too.

156
00:11:06,115 --> 00:11:08,249
[ Clears throat ]

157
00:11:08,317 --> 00:11:10,819
I'm so sorry.

158
00:11:18,127 --> 00:11:21,096
Oh. Is this
Ray's signature?

159
00:11:21,197 --> 00:11:23,765
Yes.

160
00:11:27,303 --> 00:11:30,005
[ Grunts ]

161
00:11:33,309 --> 00:11:35,076
It's getting hard to see this

162
00:11:35,144 --> 00:11:37,145
as anything other
than a suicide.

163
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:41,549
Not much of a suicide note.

164
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:44,119
"I'm sorry
for everything I've done.

165
00:11:44,220 --> 00:11:46,388
I love you."

166
00:11:46,489 --> 00:11:50,358
Man of few words.

167
00:11:50,426 --> 00:11:53,194
I know the type.

168
00:12:00,102 --> 00:12:03,538
What?

169
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:07,108
I understand a man
wanting to kill himself.

170
00:12:08,719 --> 00:12:11,179
Got to go to a pretty dark place
to take his horses with him.

171
00:12:22,662 --> 00:12:24,630
[ Dog barking in distance ]

172
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:27,475
Sheriff.

173
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:28,975
[ Sighs ]

174
00:12:29,095 --> 00:12:31,012
You mind giving me a hand
with her dressings?

175
00:12:31,138 --> 00:12:32,404
Sure.

176
00:12:37,210 --> 00:12:39,979
Shoes should have been changed
a month ago.

177
00:12:40,046 --> 00:12:41,825
Oh, you know a little bit
about horses?

178
00:12:41,945 --> 00:12:43,763
I grew up with horses.

179
00:12:43,883 --> 00:12:45,417
My dad was a farrier.

180
00:12:45,485 --> 00:12:47,119
I followed him around,

181
00:12:47,220 --> 00:12:48,787
managed to pick up
a thing or two.

182
00:12:48,855 --> 00:12:49,955
Check out her teeth.

183
00:12:58,231 --> 00:13:00,766
Teeth haven't been floated.

184
00:13:01,710 --> 00:13:03,469
Ray Stewart, by all accounts,

185
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:05,337
was a pretty serious horseman.

186
00:13:05,405 --> 00:13:07,740
Won quite a few trophies.

187
00:13:07,841 --> 00:13:09,742
Sometimes if the horses
stop winning,

188
00:13:09,843 --> 00:13:11,443
the owners stop
taking care of them.

189
00:13:11,511 --> 00:13:15,414
So, doc, she gonna make it?

190
00:13:15,515 --> 00:13:17,416
She's had some pretty bad luck.

191
00:13:17,517 --> 00:13:19,718
Burns over 50% of her body,

192
00:13:19,819 --> 00:13:21,787
and who knows what
sort of damage to the lungs.

193
00:13:21,855 --> 00:13:25,424
Well, I always
prefer the long shots.

194
00:13:25,492 --> 00:13:29,395
So whatever it costs,
whatever it takes.

195
00:13:29,496 --> 00:13:31,764
You send the bill to me.

196
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:43,042
Ruby.

197
00:13:43,143 --> 00:13:45,811
Sheriff,
before you say anything,

198
00:13:45,879 --> 00:13:48,214
I know I was supposed to
be there last night,

199
00:13:48,315 --> 00:13:52,117
and the thing is I was --
where my campsite was,

200
00:13:52,219 --> 00:13:54,853
I didn't have
any cell reception.

201
00:13:54,955 --> 00:13:57,923
Uh, it won't happen again.

202
00:13:58,024 --> 00:14:02,061
Ferg, I wasn't gonna
say anything.

203
00:14:02,128 --> 00:14:05,264
Branch: Hey, Walt,
I saw one of your campaign signs

204
00:14:05,332 --> 00:14:07,066
on the drive in.

205
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:10,302
I like them.
Kind of old-school.

206
00:14:10,403 --> 00:14:12,471
I prefer
the word "subtle."

207
00:14:12,572 --> 00:14:13,973
[ Laughs ]

208
00:14:14,074 --> 00:14:16,375
You, uh,
check that suicide note yet?

209
00:14:16,443 --> 00:14:18,177
I went ahead and got a copy

210
00:14:18,245 --> 00:14:20,045
of Ray Stewart's signature
from the DMV,

211
00:14:20,146 --> 00:14:22,948
but I couldn't find any more
substantial handwriting samples

212
00:14:23,049 --> 00:14:24,550
to compare the suicide note to.

213
00:14:24,618 --> 00:14:26,218
Bank's got
mortgage applications.

214
00:14:26,319 --> 00:14:29,388
County office should have a copy
of the deed to his ranch, so...

215
00:14:29,489 --> 00:14:31,223
[ Chuckles ] Like this?

216
00:14:31,324 --> 00:14:32,591
[ Paper rustles ]

217
00:14:32,692 --> 00:14:34,093
The ranch is
in Alice Stewart's name,

218
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,028
and there is no mortgage
application. They paid cash.

219
00:14:36,129 --> 00:14:37,730
Vic: For the truck
and horse trailer, too.

220
00:14:37,797 --> 00:14:39,465
Utility bills
are in Alice's name.

221
00:14:39,532 --> 00:14:42,167
You know, maybe she was the one
with all the dough.

222
00:14:42,269 --> 00:14:43,569
But for whatever reason,

223
00:14:43,637 --> 00:14:45,604
Ray's signature
isn't on any of the documents.

224
00:14:45,705 --> 00:14:47,206
I was thinking we should
get in touch

225
00:14:47,274 --> 00:14:48,274
with that FBI
handwriting analyst

226
00:14:48,341 --> 00:14:49,942
down in Denver.

227
00:14:50,010 --> 00:14:53,245
Nah, not worth the hassle
of involving the FBI just yet.

228
00:14:54,347 --> 00:14:56,015
Once they get a foot
in the door...

229
00:14:56,082 --> 00:14:58,550
Nothing wrong with a little
friendly competition, Walt.

230
00:14:58,618 --> 00:15:00,953
Walt: Looks like
Ray's handwriting.

231
00:15:01,054 --> 00:15:02,988
His wife and son says it was,

232
00:15:03,089 --> 00:15:06,325
so until I have reason
to suspect otherwise --

233
00:15:06,426 --> 00:15:08,460
[ dog barks in distance ]
Knock, knock!

234
00:15:08,561 --> 00:15:10,663
Look, I'm just
an insurance salesman,

235
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:12,798
but I don't see what it could be
other <i>than</i> suicide.

236
00:15:12,899 --> 00:15:14,800
The door was chained
on the inside.

237
00:15:14,901 --> 00:15:18,637
Did his life insurance
have a suicide clause?

238
00:15:18,738 --> 00:15:20,105
No.

239
00:15:20,206 --> 00:15:23,042
Because he didn't
have any life insurance.

240
00:15:23,109 --> 00:15:25,911
And the Stewarts' house
and barn structures

241
00:15:26,012 --> 00:15:27,546
weren't insured, either.

242
00:15:27,647 --> 00:15:29,615
The only policies they had

243
00:15:29,716 --> 00:15:31,850
was a life-insurance policy
on Alice,

244
00:15:31,918 --> 00:15:33,986
naming T.J.
the sole beneficiary,

245
00:15:34,087 --> 00:15:36,121
and policy all of the horses.

246
00:15:36,222 --> 00:15:37,790
Big policies on the horses.

247
00:15:37,857 --> 00:15:39,491
A couple million, all told.

248
00:15:41,594 --> 00:15:44,863
Those were top-breed
quarter horses,

249
00:15:44,964 --> 00:15:47,266
and Ray had mostly mares.

250
00:15:47,334 --> 00:15:49,234
They're easier to handle
than the stallions.

251
00:15:51,137 --> 00:15:52,805
Yeah.

252
00:15:52,872 --> 00:15:55,007
Plus, when they're
done competing,

253
00:15:55,108 --> 00:15:57,509
they make
million-dollar babies.

254
00:15:57,610 --> 00:15:58,877
It's a damn shame,
Walt, really.

255
00:16:00,513 --> 00:16:02,348
Hey, can I get a copy
of your evidence inventory

256
00:16:02,415 --> 00:16:03,916
for my claims report?

257
00:16:03,983 --> 00:16:05,217
Sure.

258
00:16:05,318 --> 00:16:09,988
So, who was the beneficiary
of the horse insurance?

259
00:16:10,056 --> 00:16:11,390
Alice.

260
00:16:14,894 --> 00:16:16,261
Bill: <i>I'm getting you</i>
<i>in there. Gonna...</i>

261
00:16:16,329 --> 00:16:18,130
<i>I'm getting</i>
<i>a full body shot there.</i>

262
00:16:18,231 --> 00:16:19,932
<i>Hey, just --</i>
<i>[ Laughs</i> ]

263
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:21,500
<i>Don't tell --</i>
<i>don't tell Ray that,</i>

264
00:16:21,601 --> 00:16:24,370
<i>but I'm getting --</i>
<i>Whoa. Whoa, be careful.</i>

265
00:16:24,437 --> 00:16:25,938
<i>Look at the camera.</i>

266
00:16:26,039 --> 00:16:28,073
<i>No, be careful.</i>
<i>You're scaring him.</i>

267
00:16:28,174 --> 00:16:30,309
[ <i>Laughs</i> ]

268
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:33,545
<i>Whoo! T.J.'s a born cowboy.</i>
<i>You kidding me?</i>

269
00:16:33,613 --> 00:16:34,980
Bill:
<i>Good riding, T.J.</i>

270
00:16:35,081 --> 00:16:36,348
Alice: <i>Hey, Bill,</i>
<i>give me the camera.</i>

271
00:16:36,449 --> 00:16:37,916
<i>No. No.</i>
<i>Yeah.</i> [ <i>Laughs</i> ]

272
00:16:37,984 --> 00:16:40,018
<i>I want to get you</i>
<i>in this movie somewhere.</i>

273
00:16:40,086 --> 00:16:41,587
<i>No, I don't want to</i>
<i>be in this --</i> [ <i>Laughs</i> ]

274
00:16:41,688 --> 00:16:43,155
Ray: <i>What was that?</i>
<i>Okay.</i>

275
00:16:43,256 --> 00:16:45,357
Yeah, yeah, look at you.
<i>Very handsome.</i>

276
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:48,327
<i>Come here.</i>
<i>Let's get the three amigos.</i>

277
00:16:48,428 --> 00:16:50,462
Whoo, look!
<i>On three, let's say "cowboy."</i>

278
00:16:50,530 --> 00:16:53,098
<i>One, two, three...</i>
<i>All: Cowboy!</i>

279
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,433
<i>Whoo!</i>

280
00:16:54,534 --> 00:16:56,101
<i>Another beautiful day</i>
<i>in Wyoming.</i>

281
00:17:00,073 --> 00:17:03,609
He won this one just, uh,
in Vegas at a competition...

282
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:05,177
Alice.
...Last year.

283
00:17:05,278 --> 00:17:06,345
Please.

284
00:17:06,446 --> 00:17:07,780
I don't know if you're doing it

285
00:17:07,881 --> 00:17:09,548
for your benefit or mine,
but right now

286
00:17:09,649 --> 00:17:11,083
I just need you to stop lying.

287
00:17:11,184 --> 00:17:12,618
Excuse me?

288
00:17:12,719 --> 00:17:14,953
I realized I never saw Ray
or any of his horses

289
00:17:15,021 --> 00:17:18,624
compete locally,
so I called Vegas and Amarillo.

290
00:17:18,725 --> 00:17:21,160
Ray didn't win any trophies.

291
00:17:21,227 --> 00:17:24,096
There wasn't even a record of
him entering the competitions.

292
00:17:24,197 --> 00:17:26,865
It's a lie.
No, no. That can't be.

293
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:29,201
And your mare, the one
that survived the fire?

294
00:17:29,302 --> 00:17:31,970
She'd been neglected for months.
No, he loved those horses.

295
00:17:32,038 --> 00:17:34,406
Well, he sure took out
a lot of insurance on 'em.

296
00:17:34,474 --> 00:17:35,974
Or rather, you did.

297
00:17:36,042 --> 00:17:37,409
What are you doing, sheriff?

298
00:17:37,477 --> 00:17:40,179
I'm trying to get you
to tell me the truth.

299
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:42,047
There's something
you're not telling me about Ray.

300
00:17:42,115 --> 00:17:44,316
N-no, there isn't.
I swear.

301
00:17:44,384 --> 00:17:47,352
Fine. If that's the case, you're
gonna be charged with murdering Ray.

302
00:17:47,454 --> 00:17:51,089
[ Scoffs ] What?
Why would I --

303
00:17:51,191 --> 00:17:53,125
Because your husband beat you.

304
00:17:55,295 --> 00:17:57,396
Or because you have
large insurance policies

305
00:17:57,497 --> 00:17:59,631
on his horses,
and you wanted that money...

306
00:17:59,732 --> 00:18:01,400
I told you --
....For you and T.J.

307
00:18:01,501 --> 00:18:04,136
This is ridiculous.
He committed suicide.

308
00:18:04,237 --> 00:18:05,471
He left a note.

309
00:18:05,572 --> 00:18:06,905
That could be forged.

310
00:18:07,006 --> 00:18:10,075
H-he chained himself in.
You said so yourself.

311
00:18:10,176 --> 00:18:13,212
There's an upstairs window.

312
00:18:13,313 --> 00:18:16,415
All you needed
was a ladder to escape.

313
00:18:17,784 --> 00:18:21,220
Alice, what are
you not telling me?

314
00:18:26,860 --> 00:18:31,463
This was the only photo
that Ray kept from before.

315
00:18:31,531 --> 00:18:34,032
Those are his parents.

316
00:18:34,133 --> 00:18:38,036
He lived in Boston.
His name was...

317
00:18:40,173 --> 00:18:42,641
...Oscar Arnesto.

318
00:18:42,709 --> 00:18:44,476
Why'd he change his name?

319
00:18:44,577 --> 00:18:48,347
He worked for the
Depanzo crime family for years.

320
00:18:50,149 --> 00:18:52,084
But he had a falling out
with them about 11 years ago,

321
00:18:52,151 --> 00:18:55,020
and he fled
with some of their money.

322
00:18:55,088 --> 00:18:57,256
I met him in Texas.

323
00:18:57,357 --> 00:19:01,793
And I just --
I just fell in love with him.

324
00:19:01,895 --> 00:19:05,330
After we were married,
he told me his secret.

325
00:19:05,431 --> 00:19:08,100
Why not make a deal
with the feds,

326
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:11,036
get some kind
of Witness Protection?

327
00:19:11,104 --> 00:19:13,739
[ Scoffs ]
Ray didn't trust the FBI.

328
00:19:13,806 --> 00:19:17,242
We just wanted a normal life.

329
00:19:17,343 --> 00:19:19,177
We bought this ranch
and the horses

330
00:19:19,245 --> 00:19:20,679
four years ago to blend in.

331
00:19:20,780 --> 00:19:22,381
So all this is a cover.

332
00:19:22,448 --> 00:19:25,083
Paid cash,
everything in your name

333
00:19:25,184 --> 00:19:27,819
so Ray couldn't
leave a paper trail.

334
00:19:27,921 --> 00:19:29,755
Yeah.

335
00:19:29,822 --> 00:19:32,791
I guess we were just
kidding ourselves.

336
00:19:32,892 --> 00:19:36,461
You can't hide
from the Depanzo family forever.

337
00:19:36,563 --> 00:19:38,430
You think they killed Ray?

338
00:19:38,531 --> 00:19:40,465
I don't know what to believe.

339
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:41,767
Either they did,

340
00:19:41,834 --> 00:19:43,802
or they drove Ray
to kill himself.

341
00:19:43,903 --> 00:19:45,370
I don't know.

342
00:19:45,471 --> 00:19:49,641
Alice, now,
you need protection.

343
00:19:49,742 --> 00:19:52,344
You should come back
to the station with me.

344
00:19:52,445 --> 00:19:54,146
We'll get T.J.
from practice.

345
00:19:54,213 --> 00:19:58,050
Ray said don't trust the police,
no matter what.

346
00:19:58,117 --> 00:20:00,786
No, he said the mob
owns the cops.

347
00:20:00,853 --> 00:20:02,654
You think I'm with the mob?

348
00:20:02,755 --> 00:20:05,757
I don't know that you're not.

349
00:20:05,858 --> 00:20:08,060
You can't stop them.

350
00:20:08,127 --> 00:20:09,561
Look, I've told you
everything that I know.

351
00:20:09,662 --> 00:20:13,131
Now, please, just go!

352
00:20:17,470 --> 00:20:18,837
So, you won't come with me?

353
00:20:18,938 --> 00:20:20,572
No, I can't.

354
00:20:22,575 --> 00:20:23,775
Okay.

355
00:20:23,843 --> 00:20:25,510
I don't have any choice.

356
00:20:25,578 --> 00:20:26,945
Alice Stewart...

357
00:20:29,315 --> 00:20:31,483
...you're under arrest.

358
00:20:31,584 --> 00:20:34,319
[ Sighs ]

359
00:20:39,173 --> 00:20:41,524
Any word from doc Bloomfield
on the autopsy?

360
00:20:41,644 --> 00:20:43,536
No, but this just in.

361
00:20:44,269 --> 00:20:46,603
"Sheriff Longmire
arrested Alice Stewart

362
00:20:46,704 --> 00:20:48,205
"and is holding her
for questioning

363
00:20:48,273 --> 00:20:50,007
"in the events
related to the barn fire

364
00:20:50,074 --> 00:20:51,775
that killed her husband,
Ray Stewart."

365
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,911
You told a reporter
before you told us, Walt.

366
00:20:53,978 --> 00:20:56,013
Nope.

367
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,015
Well, then how the hell
did he find out?

368
00:20:58,082 --> 00:21:00,818
I guess he's
a pretty good reporter.

369
00:21:00,919 --> 00:21:03,020
When were you gonna tell us
you arrested her?

370
00:21:03,087 --> 00:21:05,155
Right after I gave her
her breakfast.

371
00:21:05,223 --> 00:21:08,725
Walt. We're understaffed
enough as it is.

372
00:21:08,793 --> 00:21:10,761
If you're gonna freeze me out
of every investigation we got

373
00:21:10,862 --> 00:21:12,095
just cause I'm running
against you --

374
00:21:12,163 --> 00:21:13,330
I'm not freezing you out.

375
00:21:13,431 --> 00:21:15,532
I let you call
your handwriting expert.

376
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:19,169
Walt, this makes
all of us look bad.

377
00:21:19,237 --> 00:21:21,171
Look, once I got upstairs
to the office,

378
00:21:21,239 --> 00:21:23,040
I had every intention
of filling you in

379
00:21:23,141 --> 00:21:24,741
and asking for help.

380
00:21:24,809 --> 00:21:26,243
But if you can't wait five minutes --
We can't.

381
00:21:26,344 --> 00:21:27,878
Fine.

382
00:21:27,979 --> 00:21:29,646
Branch, I need you
to check the guest registries

383
00:21:29,714 --> 00:21:31,081
of all the local hotels
and guest ranches.

384
00:21:31,149 --> 00:21:33,083
Walt, come on, man.

385
00:21:33,151 --> 00:21:34,952
I thought you'd be a little more
excited to be the one looking

386
00:21:35,053 --> 00:21:36,820
into a possible organized-crime
connection to this case.

387
00:21:36,888 --> 00:21:38,822
The paper didn't say anything
about organized crime.

388
00:21:38,890 --> 00:21:41,592
Must be the first time the press
didn't get the whole story.

389
00:21:41,693 --> 00:21:43,827
We're looking for anybody
from the east coast,

390
00:21:43,895 --> 00:21:45,796
especially Boston.

391
00:21:45,897 --> 00:21:49,366
Can you get the door?
Hey, Walt, I got to tell you,

392
00:21:49,434 --> 00:21:51,735
I really don't like
finding out stuff like this

393
00:21:51,803 --> 00:21:52,936
in the paper.

394
00:21:53,004 --> 00:21:55,372
Do what I do.
Don't read the paper.

395
00:21:57,008 --> 00:21:59,476
You've been busy.

396
00:21:59,544 --> 00:22:01,411
I see you arrested
a distraught widow

397
00:22:01,513 --> 00:22:03,881
without anything
even approaching probable cause

398
00:22:03,982 --> 00:22:05,983
and left her traumatized son
all alone.

399
00:22:06,050 --> 00:22:07,351
I didn't leave him alone.

400
00:22:07,452 --> 00:22:09,286
I had a neighbor come get him.

401
00:22:09,354 --> 00:22:11,455
Oh, right -- Bill Hoback,
the man who's been

402
00:22:11,556 --> 00:22:13,924
on the phone all morning
with my boss.

403
00:22:13,992 --> 00:22:15,392
Hoback called a lawyer
for Alice?

404
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:18,295
Dad. [ Sighs ]

405
00:22:18,363 --> 00:22:20,764
Do you really think
that a knee-jerk,

406
00:22:20,832 --> 00:22:24,034
wrongful arrest is the best way
to kick off your campaign?

407
00:22:24,102 --> 00:22:25,402
Doesn't matter, I guess,

408
00:22:25,470 --> 00:22:27,471
because if you keep
Alice Stewart here,

409
00:22:27,572 --> 00:22:29,373
you'll probably be sued,
it'll be in the papers,

410
00:22:29,474 --> 00:22:30,774
and you'll lose the election.

411
00:22:30,842 --> 00:22:33,043
I think her life
might be in danger.

412
00:22:33,111 --> 00:22:36,213
So you're keeping her in jail
for her own protection?

413
00:22:36,281 --> 00:22:38,048
That's --
that's very noble.

414
00:22:38,116 --> 00:22:40,951
It's also kind of illegal.

415
00:22:41,019 --> 00:22:42,853
Dad.
[ Clears throat ]

416
00:22:42,921 --> 00:22:45,656
Unless you can come up
with some real evidence

417
00:22:45,757 --> 00:22:47,991
against her,
you have to let her go.

418
00:22:48,092 --> 00:22:50,160
[ Sighs ]

419
00:22:50,261 --> 00:22:52,996
Wow.
Look at that face.

420
00:22:53,097 --> 00:22:55,699
You really hate it
when I'm right, don't you?

421
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:57,267
[ Chuckles ] [ Laughs ]

422
00:23:03,141 --> 00:23:04,741
[ Door opens ]

423
00:23:04,842 --> 00:23:07,177
I tell you, Walt, this is not
the kind of sheriffing

424
00:23:07,278 --> 00:23:10,847
Absaroka county needs.

425
00:23:10,949 --> 00:23:13,717
Don't look at me.

426
00:23:13,785 --> 00:23:15,452
Look after them, Bill.

427
00:23:15,553 --> 00:23:18,055
They'll be fine.
They'll be at my place.

428
00:23:22,126 --> 00:23:24,328
Hey, T.J.

429
00:23:24,395 --> 00:23:27,230
If you want to see your horse,
just let me know.

430
00:23:27,332 --> 00:23:28,665
I can bring you by.

431
00:23:28,766 --> 00:23:30,834
So I can see her in pain?
T.J., please.

432
00:23:30,935 --> 00:23:33,870
Don't give up on her.
She hasn't.

433
00:23:33,972 --> 00:23:34,871
Let's just go.

434
00:23:38,610 --> 00:23:40,477
That is one caring
and attentive neighbor.

435
00:23:40,578 --> 00:23:42,179
Yeah.

436
00:23:42,246 --> 00:23:44,982
Why don't you follow them,
see they get to Hoback's safely?

437
00:23:45,049 --> 00:23:46,850
Make sure they don't
run off together.

438
00:23:46,951 --> 00:23:48,785
I'll see you
at doc Bloomfield's after.

439
00:23:48,886 --> 00:23:50,854
Hey, Ruby.
Uh-huh?

440
00:23:50,955 --> 00:23:53,090
You didn't tell me
Cady was waiting in my office.

441
00:23:53,157 --> 00:23:54,224
You didn't ask.

442
00:23:54,325 --> 00:23:56,893
[ Telephone rings ]

443
00:23:56,961 --> 00:23:59,229
I followed them back
to Hoback's place, Walt.

444
00:23:59,330 --> 00:24:00,564
No problems.

445
00:24:00,632 --> 00:24:02,165
Then I called
doc Bloomfield's office.

446
00:24:02,266 --> 00:24:03,567
He hasn't even
finished the autopsy yet.

447
00:24:03,635 --> 00:24:04,835
He's been
delivering twins all day.

448
00:24:04,902 --> 00:24:06,303
Do you believe that crap?

449
00:24:06,404 --> 00:24:08,572
Some people got
their priorities all messed up.

450
00:24:08,673 --> 00:24:10,407
I also checked
with a friend of mine

451
00:24:10,508 --> 00:24:12,142
who works organized crime
back east.

452
00:24:12,243 --> 00:24:15,078
He confirmed that there was
an Oscar Arnesto

453
00:24:15,179 --> 00:24:17,047
who disappeared 11 years ago.

454
00:24:17,148 --> 00:24:19,850
Your buddy think Ray and Oscar
are the same person?

455
00:24:19,917 --> 00:24:22,119
He e-mailed a picture
to my cellphone.

456
00:24:22,186 --> 00:24:23,553
It looks like Ray.

457
00:24:23,621 --> 00:24:25,222
I could send it
to your cellph--

458
00:24:25,323 --> 00:24:27,257
Oh, wait, no, I can't.
You don't have a cell--

459
00:24:27,358 --> 00:24:30,093
[ radio turns off ]

460
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:40,904
I'm agent Daxner.
Aah!

461
00:24:41,005 --> 00:24:42,706
Oh.

462
00:24:42,807 --> 00:24:47,277
Uh, you must be the, uh,
handwriting analyst.

463
00:24:47,378 --> 00:24:49,346
Federal marshal.

464
00:24:52,116 --> 00:24:54,184
I was hoping to have a talk
with your sheriff

465
00:24:54,285 --> 00:24:56,086
about this
Ray Stewart situation.

466
00:24:56,187 --> 00:24:58,422
Well, the sheriff
won't be back for a while.

467
00:24:58,523 --> 00:25:03,126
I'm Ferg--
[Sighs] Deputy Ferguson.

468
00:25:03,194 --> 00:25:04,861
Someone told me
to meet him here.

469
00:25:04,929 --> 00:25:08,331
Maybe that was Ruby?
Uh, she's out.

470
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:11,535
But you're welcome to wait.

471
00:25:13,838 --> 00:25:14,938
You wouldn't mind
if I had a word

472
00:25:15,039 --> 00:25:16,106
with Mrs. Stewart,
would you?

473
00:25:16,207 --> 00:25:17,407
You are still holding her here?

474
00:25:17,475 --> 00:25:18,942
I'm sorry.

475
00:25:19,010 --> 00:25:20,277
She -- she was released
a couple hours ago.

476
00:25:20,378 --> 00:25:21,378
You sent her home?

477
00:25:24,482 --> 00:25:26,950
She --
she's at a neighbor's house --

478
00:25:27,018 --> 00:25:28,652
uh, Bill Hoback.

479
00:25:28,753 --> 00:25:30,320
I can't believe
you released her.

480
00:25:31,289 --> 00:25:33,523
[ Sighs ]

481
00:25:33,591 --> 00:25:35,392
You should have called us.

482
00:25:37,228 --> 00:25:39,963
Listen...

483
00:25:40,031 --> 00:25:42,065
I would really appreciate it
if you could just tell me

484
00:25:42,133 --> 00:25:43,767
where I can find the sheriff.

485
00:25:43,868 --> 00:25:46,103
He's at the hospital
for the autopsy --

486
00:25:46,204 --> 00:25:47,971
just about 15 minutes away.

487
00:25:48,039 --> 00:25:49,239
It's near the golf course.

488
00:25:49,307 --> 00:25:50,407
I'll just meet him there, then.

489
00:25:55,379 --> 00:25:56,980
Ferg left word.

490
00:25:57,048 --> 00:25:59,349
A federal marshal's heading over
to ask you a few questions.

491
00:25:59,417 --> 00:26:00,650
I better work fast.

492
00:26:00,752 --> 00:26:03,320
We're gonna lose all control
over this case.

493
00:26:03,421 --> 00:26:06,156
What is this, doctor's notes?

494
00:26:06,224 --> 00:26:07,324
You can't read a damn thing.

495
00:26:09,761 --> 00:26:12,696
Ugh.

496
00:26:14,599 --> 00:26:16,666
Ugh, I hate burned bodies.

497
00:26:16,768 --> 00:26:19,069
It's so hard
to make out what's what.

498
00:26:19,137 --> 00:26:20,971
I've never seen
burns like this.

499
00:26:21,072 --> 00:26:23,707
Heat must have been
like a smelt furnace.

500
00:26:26,077 --> 00:26:26,943
Huh.

501
00:26:28,079 --> 00:26:31,948
I-I worked a suicide
back east.

502
00:26:32,049 --> 00:26:34,317
Same sort of gun --
a .45 to the side of the head,

503
00:26:34,418 --> 00:26:36,219
just like this.

504
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,522
Except there was no exit wound.

505
00:26:41,259 --> 00:26:43,960
This guy's got an exit wound,
that's for sure.

506
00:26:44,061 --> 00:26:46,163
Maybe somebody else shot him
with a different gun,

507
00:26:46,230 --> 00:26:47,697
dropped the .45
at the scene.

508
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:57,541
Nope.

509
00:26:57,608 --> 00:26:59,409
He was shot
with a .45.

510
00:27:01,679 --> 00:27:04,047
[ Sighs ]

511
00:27:04,148 --> 00:27:05,782
[ Sniffs ]

512
00:27:07,618 --> 00:27:10,120
I think I know
what the accelerant was

513
00:27:10,221 --> 00:27:14,124
that burned him this badly,
helped that fire along.

514
00:27:14,225 --> 00:27:15,492
What?

515
00:27:15,593 --> 00:27:17,794
Formaldehyde.

516
00:27:19,430 --> 00:27:21,965
[ Grunts ]

517
00:27:24,168 --> 00:27:25,669
"A coward dies many deaths.

518
00:27:25,770 --> 00:27:30,540
The valiant taste
of death but once."

519
00:27:30,608 --> 00:27:32,609
[ Coffin creaks ]

520
00:27:39,717 --> 00:27:42,252
Pardon my French,
but what the f...

521
00:27:42,353 --> 00:27:44,621
[ Sighs ]

522
00:27:46,991 --> 00:27:49,259
The reason
a .45-caliber round

523
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:52,262
doesn't leave an exit wound
in the head

524
00:27:52,363 --> 00:27:54,130
is because the brain
is gelatinous.

525
00:27:54,232 --> 00:27:56,433
It slows down the bullet.

526
00:27:56,534 --> 00:27:58,602
But if the brain tissue
wasn't there

527
00:27:58,703 --> 00:28:00,670
or shrunk down
as happens to a body

528
00:28:00,738 --> 00:28:03,306
been dead for a few years,
big old exit wound.

529
00:28:03,374 --> 00:28:04,474
And why the hell didn't you
just tell me this

530
00:28:04,542 --> 00:28:05,876
back at the hospital?

531
00:28:05,977 --> 00:28:10,347
Wasn't 100% sure
back at the hospital.

532
00:28:12,450 --> 00:28:15,685
[ Both grunt ]

533
00:28:15,753 --> 00:28:19,155
So our burn victim
is not Ray Stewart?

534
00:28:19,257 --> 00:28:21,558
Nope.
It's will Jackson.

535
00:28:21,659 --> 00:28:23,627
And how did you know
to dig here?

536
00:28:23,728 --> 00:28:27,931
I remembered seeing this
old family cemetery yesterday.

537
00:28:28,032 --> 00:28:29,499
Will's been dead five years.

538
00:28:29,567 --> 00:28:31,768
Figured Ray would go
for the freshest body.

539
00:28:31,836 --> 00:28:35,338
Then we're not dealing
with a murder or a suicide.

540
00:28:35,439 --> 00:28:39,209
Nope. We've got
a missing person.

541
00:28:55,623 --> 00:28:57,223
Walt: Looks like
they're still here.

542
00:28:57,324 --> 00:28:58,858
That's Hoback's truck.

543
00:28:58,959 --> 00:29:01,361
You think Alice knows
her husband is really alive?

544
00:29:01,428 --> 00:29:03,162
Maybe she was in on this.

545
00:29:03,264 --> 00:29:04,998
Nothing surprises me anymore.

546
00:29:05,065 --> 00:29:06,165
[ Gunshots ]

547
00:29:06,267 --> 00:29:08,401
I stand corrected.

548
00:29:08,502 --> 00:29:10,169
[ Gunfire ]

549
00:29:13,874 --> 00:29:16,075
Bill: Sheriff,
you better go away!

550
00:29:16,176 --> 00:29:17,543
Hey, Bill!

551
00:29:17,611 --> 00:29:19,178
I think you accidentally
let the safety off

552
00:29:19,246 --> 00:29:21,114
that gun of yours!

553
00:29:21,181 --> 00:29:22,982
Seriously, Walt!

554
00:29:23,083 --> 00:29:24,984
Just get out of here,
drive away!

555
00:29:25,085 --> 00:29:28,988
I can't do that, Bill.
You fired a weapon at me.

556
00:29:29,089 --> 00:29:32,425
Why don't you just
toss that gun out the door?

557
00:29:34,194 --> 00:29:35,929
[ Gunshot ]

558
00:29:35,996 --> 00:29:36,963
Aah!

559
00:29:37,064 --> 00:29:38,498
I thought you
followed them home.

560
00:29:38,599 --> 00:29:39,999
You said everything was normal.

561
00:29:40,100 --> 00:29:41,768
Everything was.
I saw the three of them go in.

562
00:29:41,835 --> 00:29:43,102
I hung out for like
half an hour.

563
00:29:43,170 --> 00:29:44,971
Nobody came out,
nobody went in.

564
00:29:45,072 --> 00:29:47,106
I guess we got to assume

565
00:29:47,174 --> 00:29:50,243
that Alice and T.J.
are in there with Bill.

566
00:29:50,344 --> 00:29:51,544
And maybe Ray, too.

567
00:29:51,645 --> 00:29:53,813
You know, if we were back east,

568
00:29:53,914 --> 00:29:56,316
we'd close the roads,
evacuate a three-block radius,

569
00:29:56,383 --> 00:29:57,784
and call in
a S.W.A.T. team.

570
00:29:57,885 --> 00:29:59,085
Well,
we don't have S.W.A.T.

571
00:30:00,554 --> 00:30:02,989
But we do have the Ferg.

572
00:30:03,090 --> 00:30:04,290
[ Vehicle approaches ]

573
00:30:14,568 --> 00:30:16,135
Get down!

574
00:30:16,203 --> 00:30:17,937
[ Gunshots ]

575
00:30:21,375 --> 00:30:24,444
Sheriff, I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

576
00:30:24,545 --> 00:30:27,013
For what, Ferg?

577
00:30:27,114 --> 00:30:28,815
The federal marshal who was
supposed to meet with you guys --

578
00:30:28,916 --> 00:30:30,416
Well, Vic said he never
showed up at the autopsy.

579
00:30:30,484 --> 00:30:32,518
So I called the number
on his business card.

580
00:30:32,586 --> 00:30:34,220
And no answer.

581
00:30:34,321 --> 00:30:36,489
And when I called
the main marshal office,

582
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:39,592
they said -- they said
they'd never even heard of him.

583
00:30:40,961 --> 00:30:42,195
The marshal was a fraud?

584
00:30:42,296 --> 00:30:44,130
What exactly did this guy
say to you, Ferg?

585
00:30:44,231 --> 00:30:46,199
He was looking
for Alice Stewart.

586
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:47,600
[ Sighs ]

587
00:30:49,670 --> 00:30:53,639
I'm thinking he found her.
You get branch over here.

588
00:30:54,908 --> 00:30:56,576
We're gonna need some backup.

589
00:30:58,345 --> 00:31:00,213
Branch: Ray's alive?

590
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:02,181
[ Gunshots ]
Is he the one shooting at us?

591
00:31:02,282 --> 00:31:04,317
I don't know.

592
00:31:04,385 --> 00:31:07,086
Could be a hit man
posing as a federal marshal.

593
00:31:07,187 --> 00:31:08,821
And Ferg told him where to go.

594
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:11,124
Accidentally.

595
00:31:11,191 --> 00:31:15,194
Hey, Walt, why don't I
call the res, get more backup?

596
00:31:15,295 --> 00:31:17,730
That'll only
make a tough situation worse.

597
00:31:17,831 --> 00:31:20,066
More guns make it tough
to negotiate.

598
00:31:20,134 --> 00:31:22,835
Is that what this is?
A negotiation?

599
00:31:28,275 --> 00:31:30,376
Let's find out.

600
00:31:30,477 --> 00:31:31,544
Hey, Billy!

601
00:31:34,181 --> 00:31:35,214
Sheriff.

602
00:31:36,316 --> 00:31:40,053
You got somebody in there
who calls himself agent Daxner?

603
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:46,325
You make sure agent Daxner knows
my number-one priority here

604
00:31:46,393 --> 00:31:47,593
is nobody gets hurt.

605
00:32:03,143 --> 00:32:05,211
Get it off!

606
00:32:05,312 --> 00:32:07,213
Get it off!

607
00:32:07,314 --> 00:32:10,583
Get it off!
Get it off!

608
00:32:10,684 --> 00:32:13,386
[ Panting, groaning ]

609
00:32:15,122 --> 00:32:16,456
Walt:
What happened to you?

610
00:32:16,557 --> 00:32:19,025
That guy, Daxner,

611
00:32:19,126 --> 00:32:21,027
he said he was
looking for Alice.

612
00:32:21,128 --> 00:32:24,363
He said he was a marshal,
so I opened the door,

613
00:32:24,465 --> 00:32:26,365
and he just went crazy.

614
00:32:26,467 --> 00:32:28,334
Are Alice and T.J. okay?

615
00:32:28,402 --> 00:32:29,669
Oh, they're scared.

616
00:32:29,736 --> 00:32:31,304
They're just --
This guy's crazy.

617
00:32:31,405 --> 00:32:33,206
What does he want?

618
00:32:33,307 --> 00:32:35,575
He said something about
wanting the money

619
00:32:35,676 --> 00:32:37,210
that Ray stole from him.

620
00:32:37,311 --> 00:32:40,346
But he -- he kept
calling Ray "Oscar."

621
00:32:40,414 --> 00:32:41,981
So, what is going on?

622
00:32:42,049 --> 00:32:45,084
So Daxner doesn't know
that Ray's actually still alive?

623
00:32:45,152 --> 00:32:47,019
No.

624
00:32:49,423 --> 00:32:50,957
[ Sighs ]

625
00:32:51,058 --> 00:32:54,327
But you do, obviously.

626
00:32:55,963 --> 00:32:57,296
Does Alice know?

627
00:32:57,397 --> 00:32:59,065
No.

628
00:33:00,701 --> 00:33:02,235
How long have you known
Ray faked his death?

629
00:33:03,670 --> 00:33:06,606
Since the night of the fire.

630
00:33:06,707 --> 00:33:10,009
When I came home that night,
he was here.

631
00:33:10,077 --> 00:33:14,213
He, uh -- he said he set
the fire to protect his family.

632
00:33:14,314 --> 00:33:16,082
But he wouldn't tell me
more than that.

633
00:33:17,985 --> 00:33:20,553
Jesus, Walt,
you got to understand.

634
00:33:20,621 --> 00:33:22,522
Ray's --
he's been a good friend.

635
00:33:22,623 --> 00:33:25,391
He saved my business
a couple years ago, and,

636
00:33:25,492 --> 00:33:26,959
you know, I owed him.

637
00:33:28,529 --> 00:33:30,830
Where is he now?
I don't know.

638
00:33:30,898 --> 00:33:32,532
I haven't seen him
since that night.

639
00:33:32,633 --> 00:33:33,966
Just talked to him
on the phone.

640
00:33:34,067 --> 00:33:37,336
Ray's cellphone
was destroyed in the fire.

641
00:33:37,437 --> 00:33:38,337
I gave him mine.

642
00:33:40,607 --> 00:33:42,108
And that's it.

643
00:33:42,209 --> 00:33:45,144
That's -- that's the truth,
Walt. I swear to you.

644
00:33:45,245 --> 00:33:47,980
Branch: He's lying.

645
00:33:48,048 --> 00:33:50,283
Phone company told me exactly
how far Hoback's cellphone is

646
00:33:50,384 --> 00:33:51,450
from the nearest cell tower.

647
00:33:51,518 --> 00:33:52,685
The cell tower is here,

648
00:33:52,786 --> 00:33:56,255
which means that phone
is on this line.

649
00:33:56,323 --> 00:33:58,057
That's right here.
Exactly.

650
00:33:58,158 --> 00:33:59,625
Hoback's phone
is inside his house.

651
00:33:59,693 --> 00:34:02,128
So either Hoback
never gave Ray the cell, or --

652
00:34:02,229 --> 00:34:03,496
Ray's not in the house, Walt.

653
00:34:03,597 --> 00:34:06,165
I swear to you.
I told you the truth.

654
00:34:08,335 --> 00:34:10,102
This weather sucks.

655
00:34:10,170 --> 00:34:12,605
Yeah.

656
00:34:19,046 --> 00:34:21,881
Branch, give me a minute.

657
00:34:21,982 --> 00:34:23,583
Do something
to draw attention to yourself.

658
00:34:23,684 --> 00:34:26,686
You're good at that.

659
00:34:40,534 --> 00:34:42,501
[ Gunshots ]

660
00:34:42,603 --> 00:34:46,272
[ Gunfire ]

661
00:35:01,321 --> 00:35:03,155
[ Gunfire ]

662
00:35:09,529 --> 00:35:13,666
Ray, you and I need to talk.

663
00:35:13,767 --> 00:35:17,403
Or should I call you Oscar?

664
00:35:20,517 --> 00:35:22,971
Just -- just let me explain,
Walt. Okay, just let me explain.

665
00:35:23,091 --> 00:35:25,087
Nobody's trying to stop you.
All right.

666
00:35:27,157 --> 00:35:29,958
They were coming for me.

667
00:35:30,026 --> 00:35:31,593
They were.

668
00:35:31,694 --> 00:35:34,063
Two weeks ago I was in town,
and I saw Lendetta.

669
00:35:34,164 --> 00:35:35,764
Who's Lendetta?

670
00:35:35,865 --> 00:35:38,434
Lendetta's
one of Depanzo's guys.

671
00:35:38,535 --> 00:35:41,770
He's probably in town
trying to work something out

672
00:35:41,871 --> 00:35:43,539
with the new casino.

673
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:46,075
I saw him in the street,
and I-I know he saw me, Walt.

674
00:35:46,176 --> 00:35:47,576
I-I know he did.

675
00:35:47,644 --> 00:35:49,578
[ Banging ]
[ Indistinct shouting ]

676
00:35:49,646 --> 00:35:50,712
Who's the guy upstairs?

677
00:35:50,814 --> 00:35:53,816
Probably one of their hit men.

678
00:35:53,917 --> 00:35:57,553
Why not just take your mob money
and get out of Absaroka county?

679
00:35:57,654 --> 00:35:59,455
That money's gone, Walt.

680
00:36:00,924 --> 00:36:04,126
I needed that insurance money
just to survive.

681
00:36:04,194 --> 00:36:06,695
I had no choice.
Can't you see that?

682
00:36:06,796 --> 00:36:10,132
I'll tell you what I see.
I see a horse murderer.

683
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:13,202
I see a grave robber.

684
00:36:13,303 --> 00:36:16,638
I see a man whose wife
and son are upstairs

685
00:36:16,739 --> 00:36:20,576
with a gun to their heads
while he's downstairs,

686
00:36:20,643 --> 00:36:23,145
warm and safe.

687
00:36:23,213 --> 00:36:24,880
[ Breathes heavily ]

688
00:36:24,948 --> 00:36:27,416
I came back here
for them, Walt.

689
00:36:27,484 --> 00:36:30,652
I came back
to take them with me!

690
00:36:30,753 --> 00:36:32,955
But he was here first.

691
00:36:33,022 --> 00:36:34,857
[ Indistinct talking
in distance ]

692
00:36:34,924 --> 00:36:39,761
I know what you're thinking.

693
00:36:39,863 --> 00:36:41,897
But I ain't no coward.

694
00:36:41,998 --> 00:36:46,768
Now, you just give me a chance,
and I can fix this.

695
00:36:46,870 --> 00:36:50,172
[ Cries ]

696
00:36:50,273 --> 00:36:52,875
Alice:
You still have a choice.

697
00:36:52,942 --> 00:36:54,343
Daxner: Shut up!

698
00:36:54,410 --> 00:36:56,678
[ Handcuffs click ]
What are you doing?

699
00:36:56,779 --> 00:36:59,781
You've been hiding out
your whole life, Ray.

700
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:05,187
You just need to hide out
a little longer.

701
00:37:05,288 --> 00:37:06,688
Walt.

702
00:37:06,756 --> 00:37:09,458
Walt!

703
00:37:13,930 --> 00:37:16,131
That wasn't exactly
what I had in mind

704
00:37:16,199 --> 00:37:17,900
as a distraction, branch.

705
00:37:18,001 --> 00:37:19,668
It worked, didn't it?

706
00:37:19,736 --> 00:37:20,769
It did.

707
00:37:20,837 --> 00:37:22,671
All right.

708
00:37:22,739 --> 00:37:24,206
I can get Daxner
to leave with me.

709
00:37:24,307 --> 00:37:26,475
Once I do, you guys go inside,

710
00:37:26,576 --> 00:37:29,645
get Alice and T.J.,
make sure they're okay.

711
00:37:29,746 --> 00:37:31,547
You'll find Ray in the cellar.

712
00:37:31,648 --> 00:37:33,815
Okay.
[ Sniffs ]

713
00:37:33,917 --> 00:37:36,919
Daxner! Hey!

714
00:37:37,020 --> 00:37:40,322
Sorry I been gone so long,

715
00:37:40,390 --> 00:37:43,192
but I think you'll appreciate
what I was up to.

716
00:37:43,293 --> 00:37:44,826
I was finding your money.

717
00:37:44,928 --> 00:37:46,562
Ray's money.

718
00:37:46,663 --> 00:37:50,899
That's what you want, right?
I can take you to it.

719
00:37:50,967 --> 00:37:53,569
Alice and the boy
don't know where it is.

720
00:37:53,670 --> 00:37:54,836
They're no use to you.

721
00:37:54,938 --> 00:37:58,540
But I know.

722
00:37:58,608 --> 00:38:00,509
If you just come with me --

723
00:38:00,577 --> 00:38:03,946
Ray: Hey!
This is Oscar Arnesto!

724
00:38:04,047 --> 00:38:07,082
You don't care about that money!
You want me!

725
00:38:07,150 --> 00:38:08,717
So come down here and get me,
you son of a bitch!

726
00:38:08,785 --> 00:38:10,219
I ain't afraid of you!

727
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,753
[ Gunfire ]

728
00:38:15,124 --> 00:38:17,059
[ Gunfire continues ]

729
00:38:30,707 --> 00:38:32,174
[ Grunting, groaning ]

730
00:39:01,137 --> 00:39:02,671
[ Grunts ]

731
00:39:02,739 --> 00:39:03,739
[ Daxner coughs ]

732
00:39:15,285 --> 00:39:18,920
[ Panting ] Oh, no.

733
00:39:18,988 --> 00:39:20,889
[ Panting ]

734
00:39:23,359 --> 00:39:28,563
Why didn't you stay quiet?

735
00:39:28,631 --> 00:39:31,633
[ Weakly ] I told you
I wasn't a coward.

736
00:39:56,125 --> 00:39:58,694
I know I was a favor.

737
00:39:58,761 --> 00:40:00,929
I only got hired 'cause you were
helping out my dad.

738
00:40:02,765 --> 00:40:08,403
I'm just --
I'm not cut out for this.

739
00:40:12,842 --> 00:40:15,610
Ferg, I hired you
for two reasons.

740
00:40:15,678 --> 00:40:18,013
Yes, one was a favor
to your father.

741
00:40:18,114 --> 00:40:20,315
And the other?

742
00:40:26,322 --> 00:40:28,223
I'm still waiting to find out.

743
00:40:28,324 --> 00:40:30,959
[ Telephone rings ]

744
00:40:35,131 --> 00:40:36,898
Pick up your badge, deputy.

745
00:40:36,966 --> 00:40:39,768
[ Footsteps ]

746
00:40:39,869 --> 00:40:42,904
[ Music ]

747
00:40:42,972 --> 00:40:44,306
Walt.

748
00:40:45,241 --> 00:40:47,142
Vet's on the phone.

749
00:41:03,926 --> 00:41:07,729
You don't have to
do this anymore.

750
00:41:07,830 --> 00:41:11,666
You already
proved how tough you are.

751
00:41:15,238 --> 00:41:17,472
It's okay to go.

752
00:41:19,809 --> 00:41:21,843
It's okay.

753
00:41:40,196 --> 00:41:42,197
[ Sighs ]

754
00:41:42,298 --> 00:41:48,069
"Know when to fight
and when to seek peace.

755
00:41:48,171 --> 00:41:50,906
"For as long
as the moon shall rise,

756
00:41:51,007 --> 00:41:54,209
"as long
as the rivers shall flow,

757
00:41:54,310 --> 00:41:58,880
"as long as the sun will shine,

758
00:41:58,948 --> 00:42:03,318
let us all
know peace."

759
00:42:05,121 --> 00:42:07,722
[ Horse snorts ]

760
00:42:07,824 --> 00:42:10,125
[ Music continues ]

761
